message_1: What is the cardinality of the set of all functions from a set A with 5 elements to a set B with 2 elements?
message_2:
The cardinality of the set of all functions from a set A with 5 elements to a set B with 2 elements can be found using the formula:

Cardinality = |B|^|A|

In this case, |A| = 5 (since there are 5 elements in set A) and |B| = 2 (since there are 2 elements in set B).

Cardinality = 2^5 = 32

So, the cardinality of the set of all functions from a set A with 5 elements to a set B with 2 elements is 32.
